Graph data structure nodes (vertices) aur edges se milkar banta hai. Ye relationships ko model karne ke liye useful hai. Graph ko implement karne ka ek simple tarika adjacency list hai. Yeh raha ek example JavaScript me:

```javascript
class Graph {
    constructor() {
        this.adjacencyList = {};
    }

    addVertex(vertex) {
        if (!this.adjacencyList[vertex]) {
            this.adjacencyList[vertex] = [];
        }
    }

    addEdge(v1, v2) {
        this.adjacencyList[v1].push(v2);
        this.adjacencyList[v2].push(v1);
    }
}

const graph = new Graph();
graph.addVertex('A');
graph.addVertex('B');
graph.addEdge('A', 'B');
console.log(graph.adjacencyList);
```

Is example me humne ek graph create kiya hai jisme vertices aur edges add kiye gaye hain. Is tarah aap kisi bhi complex relationship ko model kar sakte hain.

