DNS yaani Domain Name System, internet ka phonebook hai. Jab hum kisi website ka naam type karte hain, jaise 'google.com', toh DNS us naam ko IP address mein convert karta hai. Yeh conversion is liye zaroori hai kyunki computers sirf numbers ko samajhte hain. Ye process is tarah se hoti hai:

1. Jab aap 'google.com' enter karte hain, toh aapka computer sabse pehle local DNS cache check karta hai.
2. Agar wahan nahi mila, toh wo ISP (Internet Service Provider) ke DNS server se query karta hai.
3. Agar wahan bhi nahi mila, toh wo authoritative DNS server tak jata hai.

Yeh process kuch aise hoti hai:

```javascript
function resolveDNS(domain) {
    // Check local cache
    if (localCache[domain]) {
        return localCache[domain];
    }
    // Check ISP DNS
    const ipFromISP = queryISP(domain);
    if (ipFromISP) {
        return ipFromISP;
    }
    // Check authoritative DNS
    const ipFromAuthoritative = queryAuthoritativeDNS(domain);
    return ipFromAuthoritative;
}
```

