Database normalization ek process hai jiska maqsad data redundancy ko kam karna aur data integrity ko barhawa dena hota hai. Isme data ko multiple tables me organize kiya jata hai taake data efficiently store aur maintain kiya ja sake. Pehle normal form (1NF) ka matlab hai ke table me har column ko atomic value deni chahiye. Iska ek example:

```sql
-- Before Normalization
CREATE TABLE Students (
    StudentID INT,
    Name VARCHAR(100),
    Subjects VARCHAR(255)
);

-- After Normalization
CREATE TABLE Students (
    StudentID INT,
    Name VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE Subjects (
    SubjectID INT,
    StudentID INT,
    SubjectName VARCHAR(100)
);
```

Yahan pe pehle table me subjects ko comma-separated list me rakha gaya tha, lekin normalization ke baad subjects ko alag table me rakh diya gaya hai.

