Stack ek linear data structure hai jo Last In First Out (LIFO) principle par kaam karta hai. Iska matlab hai ke jo cheez sabse pehle add ki gayi thi wo sabse aakhri remove hoti hai. Stack ko do main operations hote hain: push (item add karna) aur pop (item remove karna). 

Example in Python: 
```python
class Stack:
    def __init__(self):
        self.items = []

    def push(self, item):
        self.items.append(item)

    def pop(self):
        return self.items.pop() if not self.is_empty() else None

    def is_empty(self):
        return len(self.items) == 0
``` 
Is code mein aap Stack class bana rahe hain aur push aur pop methods define kar rahe hain.

