Big O notation performance ya complexity ko analyze karne ka tarika hai. Yeh batata hai ke kisi algorithm ka time ya space complexity kis tarah se input size ke saath badalta hai. Jaise ke O(1) constant time, O(n) linear time, aur O(n^2) quadratic time. Aayiye ek example dekhte hain:

```python
# O(n) complexity:
def linear_search(arr, target):
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        if arr[i] == target:
            return i
    return -1

# O(n^2) complexity:
def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
                arr[j], arr[j+1] = arr[j+1], arr[j]
    return arr
```

Recursion ek aisi technique hai jisme ek function apne aap ko call karta hai. Yeh tab tak chalta hai jab tak koi base case nahi mil jata. Misal ke taur par, agar hume factorial nikalna ho, to hum function ko n k liye call karte hain, jo n-1 ka factorial nikalta hai. Yeh process chalta rahta hai jab tak n 1 nahi ho jata. 

Example: 
```python
def factorial(n):
    if n == 1:
        return 1
    else:
        return n * factorial(n - 1)
```
Is function ko bulaane par, yeh apne aap ko n-1 ke liye call karega jab tak n 1 nahi ho jata.

