JavaScript mein variables declare karne ke liye `var`, `let`, aur `const` teen tarike hain, lekin inka istemal kuch alag hai:

1. **var** - Ye function-scoped hota hai. Iska matlab ye hai ke agar aap isse function ke andar declare karte hain, to ye sirf us function ke andar accessible hota hai. 
   Example: 
   ```
   function example() {
       var x = 10;
       if (true) {
           var x = 20; // same variable!
           console.log(x); // 20
       }
       console.log(x); // 20
   }
