Recursion aik programming concept hai jismein function khud ko call karta hai. Iska use problems ko choti sub-problems mein todne ke liye kiya jata hai. Har call ke sath ek base case hona chahiye jisse recursion ruk jaaye. Yahan par aik example hai factorial nikalne ka:

```javascript
function factorial(n) {
    if (n === 0) {
        return 1;  // Base case
    }
    return n * factorial(n - 1);  // Recursive case
}

console.log(factorial(5));  // Output: 120
```
Is example mein, `factorial` function khud ko call karta hai jab tak wo base case tak nahi pahunchta. Is tarah se recursion kaam karta hai.

