Tree data structure hierarchical structure hota hai jo nodes se milkar banta hai. Har tree mein ek root node hoti hai, jo sab nodes ka parent hota hai, aur baqi nodes uski children hoti hain. Yahan ek simple tree ka example hai:

```javascript
class Node {
    constructor(value) {
        this.value = value;
        this.children = [];
    }
}

class Tree {
    constructor(rootValue) {
        this.root = new Node(rootValue);
    }

    addChild(parentValue, childValue) {
        const parentNode = this.findNode(this.root, parentValue);
        if (parentNode) {
            parentNode.children.push(new Node(childValue));
        }
    }

    findNode(node, value) {
        if (node.value === value) return node;
        for (let child of node.children) {
            const result = this.findNode(child, value);
            if (result) return result;
        }
        return null;
    }
}

let myTree = new Tree('Root');
myTree.addChild('Root', 'Child 1');
myTree.addChild('Root', 'Child 2');
```

Is example mein humne Node aur Tree classes banayi hain, jo tree structure ko represent karti hain.

