Array aur Linked List dono hi data structure hain, magar inke beech kuch ahem farq hain. 

1. **Storage**: Array mein data contiguous memory locations mein store hota hai, jabke Linked List mein data nodes ke tor par store hota hai jahan har node agle node ka reference rakhti hai. 

2. **Size**: Array ka size fixed hota hai jabke Linked List ka size dynamic hota hai. Aap Linked List mein asani se nodes add ya remove kar sakte hain. 

3. **Access Time**: Array mein elements ko direct index se access kiya ja sakta hai, jo ke O(1) time complexity mein hota hai, jabke Linked List mein elements ko access karne ke liye traversal karna padta hai, jo ke O(n) time complexity mein hota hai.

Example:
- Array: 
```javascript
let myArray = [10, 20, 30, 40]; // Fixed size
console.log(myArray[2]); // Accessing element at index 2
```

- Linked List: 
```javascript
class Node {
    constructor(data) {
        this.data = data;
        this.next = null;
    }
}

class LinkedList {
    constructor() {
        this.head = null;
    }
}
```
In short, agar aapko fixed size aur fast access chahiye to Array use karo, aur agar aapko flexible size chahiye to Linked List best hai.

JavaScript mein variables declare karne ke liye teen keywords hain: `let`, `const`, aur `var`. Inka use karne ka tarika aur scope mein farq hai. 

