   ```

In dono ka istemal aapki zaroorat par depend karta hai.

useEffect hook React mein ek powerful feature hai jo functional components mein side effects ko manage karne ke liye istemal hota hai. Iska istamal lifecycle methods ki tarah hota hai, jaise componentDidMount, componentDidUpdate, aur componentWillUnmount. Example ke liye:

```javascript
import React, { useEffect, useState } from 'react';

function ExampleComponent() {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

    useEffect(() => {
        document.title = `Count: ${count}`;
    }, [count]); // Yahan [count] dependency array hai

    return (
        <div>
            <p>Count: {count}</p>
            <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increment</button>
        </div>
    );
}
```
Is example mein, jab bhi 'count' change hota hai, useEffect hook document title ko update karta hai.

