Graph aik aisi data structure hai jisme nodes aur edges hote hain. Nodes ko vertices bhi kehate hain aur edges un nodes ke darmiyan connections hote hain. Graph ko do tarikon se represent kiya ja sakta hai: adjacency matrix ya adjacency list. 

Yahan aik simple example hai adjacency list ka:

```python
# Graph ko adjacency list se represent karna
class Graph:
    def __init__(self):
        self.graph = {}

    def add_edge(self, u, v):
        if u not in self.graph:
            self.graph[u] = []
        self.graph[u].append(v)

    def print_graph(self):
        for node in self.graph:
            print(f'{node} -> {self.graph[node]}')

# Graph ka istemal
g = Graph()
g.add_edge(1, 2)
g.add_edge(1, 3)
g.add_edge(2, 4)
g.print_graph()
```

Is example mein, humne nodes aur edges add kiye hain aur phir graph ko print kiya hai.

