Data structures ke interview mein aksar kuch basic concepts aur inki implementation puchhi jati hain. Jaise ke, aap se binary tree, linked list, stack, aur queue ke baare mein pucha ja sakta hai. Aapko kisi bhi data structure ki complexity aur use-case bhi samjhana padega. Example ke liye, yahan ek simple linked list ka code hai:

```python
class Node:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.next = None

class LinkedList:
    def __init__(self):
        self.head = None

    def append(self, data):
        new_node = Node(data)
        if not self.head:
            self.head = new_node
            return
        last = self.head
        while last.next:
            last = last.next
        last.next = new_node
```

Is tarah ke sawalat aapko data structures ke basic samajhne aur unhe implement karne mein madad karte hain.

Tree data structure ek hierarchical structure hai jahan ek root node hota hai aur iske children nodes hote hain. Har node mein data hota hai aur iske zero ya zyada children ho sakte hain. Tree ka ek basic structure is tarah hota hai:

```python
class TreeNode:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data
        self.children = []

    def add_child(self, child):
        self.children.append(child)
```

Iske ilawa, binary tree ek khas tree hai jahan har node ke do children hote hain. Tree ko search, insert, aur delete karne ke liye bhi algorithms hain jo aapko interview mein puchhe ja sakte hain.

Generators ka sab se bada faida memory efficiency hai. Ye data ko ek waqt par generate karte hain, is liye aapko poora data memory mein nahi rakhna padta. Ye especially tab faida mand hote hain jab aapko bohot saare data points ya sequences ki zaroorat hoti hai. Example:

