SQL injection ek security vulnerability hai jisme attacker SQL queries mein malicious code inject kar sakta hai. Yeh aksar tab hota hai jab user input ko bina validation ke direct SQL query mein istemal kiya jata hai. Isse attacker database ko access kar sakta hai, data manipulate kar sakta hai ya delete kar sakta hai. Isse bachne ke liye humein parameterized queries ya prepared statements istemal karni chahiye. Example: 

// Vulnerable Example
let userInput = '1 OR 1=1';
let query = `SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ${userInput}`;

// Safe Example using Prepared Statement
const sql = 'SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?';
const params = [userInput];
database.execute(sql, params);

Big O notation ek mathematical concept hai jo algorithms ki efficiency ya performance ko measure karne ke liye istemal hota hai. Yeh worst-case scenario ko represent karta hai, yani sabse zyada time ya space jo algorithm consume karega jab yeh input size bada ho. Common Big O notations hain: O(1), O(n), O(log n), O(n^2) etc. Example: 

// O(1) Example
function getFirstElement(arr) {
    return arr[0]; // Yeh constant time mein execute hota hai
}

// O(n) Example
function printAllElements(arr) {
    for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        console.log(arr[i]); // Yeh input size ke hisaab se time leta hai
    }
}

// O(n^2) Example
function printPairs(arr) {
    for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        for(let j = 0; j < arr.length; j++) {
            console.log(arr[i], arr[j]); // Yeh nested loops hain
        }
    }
}

CORS ka matlab hai Cross-Origin Resource Sharing. Ye ek security feature hai jo web browsers ko allow karta hai ke sirf specific domains se resources access kar sakein. Agar aapka frontend aur backend alag domains par hain, to aapko CORS errors ka samna karna pad sakta hai. Iska fix karne ka tareeqa ye hai ke server par CORS headers set karein. Misal ke tor par, agar aap Node.js istemal kar rahe hain:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const cors = require('cors');
const app = express();

app.use(cors()); // Ye line CORS ko enable karti hai

app.get('/api/data', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ message: 'Hello World' });
});

app.listen(3000, () => console.log('Server running on port 3000')); 
```

Is se aapka server requests ko accept karega jo different origin se aati hain.

CORS ka matlab hai Cross-Origin Resource Sharing. Ye ek security feature hai jo browser ko allow karta hai ke wo sirf same origin (domain) se resources ko access kare. Agar aap kisi doosre domain se API call karte hain aur CORS properly configure nahi hai, toh aapko CORS error nazar aayega. Isay fix karne ke liye, server side per proper headers set karna hote hain. Jaise ke:

```javascript
// Node.js Express server example
app.use((req, res, next) => {
    res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*'); // Ya specific origin set karein
    res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Origin, X-Requested-With, Content-Type, Accept');
    next();
});
```

Is code mein `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header ko set kiya gaya hai.

Tree data structure ek hierarchical structure hai jahan nodes ko parent-child relationship ke saath organize kiya jata hai. Har tree ka ek root node hota hai, jo sabse upar hota hai. Uske neeche child nodes hote hain. Ek simple binary tree ka structure kuch is tarah hota hai:

```javascript
class Node {
    constructor(value) {
        this.value = value;
        this.left = null;
        this.right = null;
    }
}

class Tree {
    constructor() {
        this.root = null;
    }
}
