Binary search algorithm ek efficient searching technique hai jo sorted array mein kisi element ko dhoondne ke liye use hoti hai. Is algorithm mein hum array ko half karte hain aur decide karte hain ke dhoondha gaya element kis half mein hai. Ye process tab tak chalta hai jab tak element mil nahi jata ya array khatam nahi ho jata. Yahan ek simple code example hai:

```python
def binary_search(arr, target):
    low = 0
    high = len(arr) - 1
    while low <= high:
        mid = (low + high) // 2
        if arr[mid] == target:
            return mid  # Element found
        elif arr[mid] < target:
            low = mid + 1  # Search in right half
        else:
            high = mid - 1  # Search in left half
    return -1  # Element not found
```

Is code mein, `arr` sorted array hai aur `target` wo element hai jo aap dhoond rahe hain.

